$ systemcpl.dll

`systemcpl.dll` implements the (My) *System → Windows/control-panel* which allows to view information about the computer, and change settings for hardware, performance, and remote connections.

This control panel is especially useful to quickly determine a computer's name, the available amount of memory, installed CPU, the → Windows/versions[Windows version] etc.

The control panel can be opened with the → Windows/keyboard-shortcuts[keyboard shortcut] `win + break/pause`.
In a console (→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`], → Windows/PowerShell), it can be started with
code {
C:\> → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/control_exe[control] system
C:\> → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/control_exe[control] /name microsoft.system
code }

gh|Windows-Pics|/Windows/System32/systemcpl.dll.png||

{ Change settings

  A mouse click on *Change settings* takes the user to → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/sysdm_cpl[System Properties].

}
